modules.name: React
modules.comments: This module defines foreign types and functions which wrap React's functionality.

declarations.comments: A virtual DOM node, or component.
declarations.title: UI

declarations.comments: A reference to a component, essentially React's `this`.
declarations.title: UIRef

declarations.comments: An event handler. The type argument represents the type of the event.
declarations.title: EventHandler

declarations.comments: This phantom type indicates that both read and write access to a resource are disallowed.
declarations.title: Disallowed

declarations.comments: This phantom type indicates that read access to a resource is allowed.
declarations.title: Read

declarations.comments: This phantom type indicates that write access to a resource is allowed.
declarations.title: Write

declarations.comments: This phantom type indicates that only read access to a resource is allowed.
declarations.title: Only

declarations.comments: An access synonym which indicates that both read and write access are allowed.
declarations.title: ReadWrite

declarations.comments: An access synonym which indicates that reads are allowed but writes are not.
declarations.title: ReadOnly

declarations.comments:
This effect indicates that a computation may read or write the component state.

The first type argument is either `ReadWrite`, `ReadOnly` or `Disallowed` dependeding on the context.

The second type argument is the type of the state of the component.
declarations.title: ReactState

declarations.comments: This effect indicates that a computation may read the component props.
declarations.title: ReactProps

declarations.comments:
This effect indicates that a computation may read the component refs.

The first type argument is either `ReadOnly` or `Disallowed` dependeding on the context.
declarations.title: ReactRefs

declarations.comments: The type of refs objects.
declarations.title: Refs

declarations.comments: The type of DOM events.
declarations.title: Event

declarations.comments: The type of mouse events.
declarations.title: MouseEvent

declarations.comments: The type of keyboard events.
declarations.title: KeyboardEvent

declarations.comments: A function which handles events.
declarations.title: EventHandlerContext

declarations.comments: A rendering function.
declarations.title: Render

declarations.comments: A specification of a component.
declarations.title: UISpec

declarations.comments: Create a component specification.
declarations.title: spec

declarations.comments: Read the component props.
declarations.title: getProps

declarations.comments: Read the component refs.
declarations.title: getRefs

declarations.comments: Write the component state.
declarations.title: writeState

declarations.comments: Read the component state.
declarations.title: readState

declarations.comments: Transform the component state by applying a function.
declarations.title: transformState

declarations.comments: Create a component from a component spec.
declarations.title: mkUI

declarations.comments: Create an event handler.
declarations.title: handle

declarations.comments: Render a component as a string.
declarations.title: renderToString

declarations.comments: Render a component to the document body.
declarations.title: renderToBody

declarations.comments: Render a component to the element with the specified ID.
declarations.title: renderToElementById
